   386→                        <div id="content">For a graph $G$ let $\tau(G)$ denote the minimal number of vertices that include at least one from each maximal clique of $G$ on at least two vertices (sometimes called the clique transversal number).<br><br>Let $H(n)$ be maximal such that every triangle-free graph on $n$ vertices contains an independent set on $H(n)$ vertices.<br><br>If $G$ is a graph on $n$ vertices then is\[\tau(G)\leq n-H(n)?\]</div>
